description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NHS West Sussex are looking for an exceptional candidate for the role of Head of Urgent Care. The role is critical to the delivery of Integrated Urgent Care across the West Sussex ‘place’ and links in to the strategic programme of work across the Sussex Health and Care Partnership ICS. The role also has a lead role in the delivery of the West Sussex Stroke Programme.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will bring significant experience of working in health and/or social care and will have excellent programme and project management skills. The role would be suited to candidates with a clinical background but this is not essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be flexible in approach and have a strong track record of delivering programmes and projects in complex organisations/systems, with a ‘can do’ attitude and a willingness to work collaboratively with system partners. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NHS West Sussex is working together with NHS Brighton and Hove CCG and NHS East Sussex CCG as part of the Sussex ICS – the Sussex Health and Care Partnership. Sussex CCGs are values based organisations who are proud to embed the CCG values in to everything we do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
